; RPZ trigger test zone (Sprint 47 task #604).
;
; Covers the three post-resolution trigger types and one intra-zone tie-break:
;
;   (i)   Response-IP   — block 198.51.100.1/32 (TEST-NET-3, RFC 5737).
;   (ii)  NSIP          — block NS IP 203.0.113.1/32 (TEST-NET-3).
;   (iii) NSDNAME       — block NS named blocked-ns.example.com.
;   (iv)  Tie-break     — QNAME NXDOMAIN (priority 1) beats Response-IP NODATA
;                         (priority 3) for tie-break.example.com.

$ORIGIN rpz-triggers.test.
$TTL 30
@ IN SOA ns1 hostmaster 1 3600 900 604800 30

; (i) Response-IP: block 198.51.100.1 → NXDOMAIN
; RPZ encoding: 32.<reversed-octets>.rpz-ip  (198.51.100.1 → 1.100.51.198)
32.1.100.51.198.rpz-ip   IN CNAME .

; (ii) NSIP: block NS server IP 203.0.113.1 → NXDOMAIN
; RPZ encoding: 32.<reversed-octets>.rpz-nsip  (203.0.113.1 → 1.113.0.203)
32.1.113.0.203.rpz-nsip  IN CNAME .

; (iii) NSDNAME: block NS named blocked-ns.example.com. → NXDOMAIN
blocked-ns.example.com.rpz-nsdname   IN CNAME .

; (iv) Tie-break: QNAME NXDOMAIN for tie-break.example.com. (priority 1)
tie-break.example.com    IN CNAME .

; (iv) Tie-break: Response-IP NODATA for 10.99.99.99 (priority 3, loses to QNAME)
; RPZ encoding: 32.99.99.99.10.rpz-ip  (10.99.99.99 → 99.99.99.10)
32.99.99.99.10.rpz-ip    IN CNAME *.
